pīyūṣaṃ parimathateti paryaśāstvam ||3||
brahmā-ādyai:	by Brahmaa and other gods
stuta-mahimā ciraṃ	being sung Thy excellences for long
tadānīṃ	at that time
prāduṣṣan	appearing
varada	O Bestower of Boons!
pura:	in front (of them)
pareṇa dhāmnā	with supreme glory (commanded)
he devā	O Gods!
ditija-kulai:-	with the Asuras,
vidhāya sandhiṃ	making peace,
pīyūṣaṃ parimathata-	nectar churn out
iti paryaśā:-tvam	thus commanded Thee
Brahmaa and the other gods sung Thy excellences for long. O Bestower of Boons! Thou then manifested Thyself before them in great glory and commanded them to make peace with the Asuras and then prepare to churn the milk ocean for nectar.

00:00:57.905 --> 00:01:17.642
sandhānaṃ kṛtavati dānavai: suraughe
manthānaṃ nayati madena mandarādrim |
bhraṣṭe'smin badaramivodvahan khagendre
sadyastvaṃ vinihitavān paya:payodhau ||4||
sandhānaṃ kṛtavati	having made peace
dānavai: suraughe	with the Asuras by the gods
manthānaṃ nayati	when carrying the churning rod
madena mandara-adrim	with great pride, the Mandara mountain
bhraṣṭe-asmin	(when) it fell down
badaram-iva-udvahan	as a berry picking it up
khagendre sadya:-tvam	On Garuda immediately Thou
vinihitavān	placed it
paya:payodhau	in the milk ocean
Devas made peace with the Asuras and with great pride carried the Mandara mountain for use as a churning rod. The mountain fell from their hands on the way. Then Thou seated on Garuda, picked it up as if it were a tiny berry and installed it in the milk ocean.

00:01:17.642 --> 00:01:36.890
ādhāya drutamatha vāsukiṃ varatrāṃ
