kṣubhita-jala-udare	in the waters fully stirred
tadānīṃ	then
dugdha-abdhau	of the milk ocean
gurutara-bhārata:	because of its (mountain's) heavy weight
nimagne	sank
deveṣu vyathitatameṣu	the Devas becoming very worried
tat-priyaiṣī	their (the Deva's) wellwisher (Thou)
prāṇaiṣī:	assumed
kamaṭha-tanuṃ	a tortoise form
kaṭhora-pṛṣṭhām	with a hard back
When the Mandara mountain as a churning rod had fully stirred the waters of the milk ocean to its depth, it sank due to its own weight. The Devas became very worried. Thee who are their well wisher, assumed the form of a tortoise with a hard back.

00:01:56.301 --> 00:02:14.733
vajrātisthiratarakarpareṇa viṣṇo
