viṣṇo	O All Pervading being!
vistārāt-	and in extent (width)
parigata-lakṣa-yojanena	exceeding a lakh of Yojanas
ambhodhe: kuhara-gatena	(the rod) which had sunk deep into the ocean
varṣmaṇā tvaṃ	with such a body Thou
nirmgnaṃ kṣitidharanātham-	the great mountain which had sunk (into the sea)
unninetha	(Thou) lifted up
O All pervading Being! by diving deep into the ocean Thou lifted up the sinking mountain on Thy back which was harder than a thunderbolt and more than a lakh of Yojanas in width.

00:02:14.733 --> 00:02:33.165
unmagne jhaṭiti tadā dharādharendre
nirmethurdṛḍhamiha sammadena sarve |
