udbhrāmyat	ejecting up
bahu-timi-nakra-cakravāle	many fish crocodiles and other aquatic creatures
tatra-abdhau	there (when) the ocean
cira-mathite-api	in spite being churned for long
nirvikāre	remained unchanged
eka:-tvaṃ	Thou alone
kara-yuga-kṛṣṭa-sarparāja:	with (Thy) two hands pulled the (two ends) of the serpent king
saṃrājan	shining brightly
pavanapureśa	O Lord of Guruvaayur!
pāhi rogāt	relieve (me of my) diseases
In spite of being churned for long, the ocean remained unchanged, though many fish crocodile and other aquatic creatures were thrown up. Thou alone, then, shining brilliantly, with Thy two hands pulled the two ends of the serpent. O Lord of Guruvaayur! Relieve me of my diseases.
